author: jeremias
msg: Funny, why didn't I realize that the sorting didn't occur as it should have? Higher values in the priority file now mean higher priority. The effect: Image IO codecs are now properly preferred over the internal codecs. In a Sun JDK 1.3 environment, the internal ImageWriters will be chosen.

author: jeremias
msg: Avoid an NPE in close() when there is something going wrong in the writeImage() call before (and close() being called in a finally section).

author: epunzalan
msg: Fixed missing prompt for parameters when doing release:perform on a project where release:prepare is done outside of continuum.

author: thorsten
msg: Activating enhanced caching. We are using now an AggregateValidity over all contracts and their raw data
(if exists). Still we can move some methods (marked with *) to the startDocument method and make the jx
generator cacheable. You can turn the caching on/off by either define it in your f.p.x or on a request base
by adding "?dispatcher.caching=off" to the requested url.
